 of the fourth game Luzhin pushed back the piece moved by his father and with a shake of his head said in a confident unchildlike voice: 'The worst reply. Chigorin suggests taking the Pawn.'

And when with incomprehensible, hopeless speed he had lost this game as well, Luzhin senior again laughed, and with trembling hand began to pour milk into a cut-glass tumbler, on the bottom of which lay a raspberry core, which now floated to the surface and circled, unwilling to be extracted, His son put aw